A rational number is a number which can be written as a fraction a/b where a and b are integers.  eg. 5, 0.3, 1(1/5), -1.79(-179/100), ð9

Irrational numbers are decimals which repeat (not a fixed length).  eg. ð11, ð2, Ð, e, surds.
@endnode

