@node M1Comp "M1: Finding Components of Forces"
@{u}Finding Components of Forces@{uu}

When you only have one force, you can draw a triangle and work out x and y by:

r is the resultant force
x is the side adjacent to the angle ø
y is the side opposite the angle.

x = r cos ¤
y = r sin ¤

When you know x and y, the resultant force r and angle ¤ can be found:

