@node M1Project "M1: Projectiles"
@{u}Projectiles@{uu}

A prjectile is something thrown into the air.  If air resistance is ignored and the motion is subject to gravity, then the path of the projectile is a parabola.

We shall split the motion into horizontal and vertical @{"components" link M1Comp}.  

Horizontally there are no forces acting and the motion will be under constant velocity (acceleration = 0).

The vertical motion is subject to gravity and therefore is at a constant @{"acceleration" link M1Accel} of 9.8m/s² downwards.
