                                                 T²

Potential energy is the energy a body possesses because of its position.  Potential energy is always relative to some defined base level.

pe = mgh (mass × gravity × height)
   = force due to gravity (mg) × distance (h)

Potential energy is the @{"work" link M1Work} done against gravity in raising an object a height h.

Another way of looking at the @{"work" link M1Work} done against @{"gravity" link M1Gravity} is to look at work done against the @{"component" link M1Comp} of the weight down the plane.
