@node T1Summary "T1: Methods for Summarising Sample Data"
@{u}Methods for summarising sample data@{uu}

There are two main types of statistic that we have to consider.  The first is measures of correlation, which give an indication of how the data is focused or centred.  The second are measures of dispersion, which give an indication of how the data is spread.

@{"Measures of location  " link T1Locate}
@{"Measures of dispersion" link T1Dispersion}
@endnode

